      <h1 class='title'>Chemical Weapons</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 28 March 2003 vol 402 c32WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_32ws' title='Col. 32WS &mdash; HC Deb 28 March 2003 vol 402 c32WS' name='column_32ws' href='#column_32ws' rel='bookmark'>32WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0402P0-04996'>
        <a name='S6CV0402P0_20030328_CWS_11'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-nigel-griffiths' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0402P0_20030328_CWS_11' title='Link to this speech by Mr Nigel Griffiths' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-nigel-griffiths" title="Mr Nigel Griffiths">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Trade and Industry (Nigel Griffiths)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0402P0-04996">I have appointed Dr J Marriott, the new Government Chemist to the Committee for a period of three years. He replaces Dr Worswick, the former Government Chemist.</p>
        </blockquote>
